{
  "title": "ISic003130. Relief-carved disk engraved by Alkimos",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Giorgia Capra</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἄλκιμος\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἄλκιμος\">Ἄλκιμος</span></span> ἔγλυψε </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Giorgia Capra</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἄλκιμος\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἄλκιμος\">ΑΛΚΙΜΟΣ</span></span>ΕΓΛΥΨΕ</span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic003130_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Image reproduced under fair use from www.mfa.org (https://collections.mfa.org/download/151092)\" src=\"ISic003130_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003130.jpg\"><img title=\"Image reproduced under fair use from www.mfa.org (https://collections.mfa.org/download/151092)\" src=\"ISic003130-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>Text derived from photograph</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1030-5679\">Giorgia Capra</a></p>  <p>Alkimos engraved.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>Vermeule and Comstock suggest that the relief style implies that Alkimos was perhaps a coin die engraver; they also note that the eight-point star first appears in Sicily on Syracusan coinage from c.400 BCE. For the museum's record (Sculpture in Stone (MFA), no. 089; Sculpture in Stone and Bronze (MFA), p. 109) see <a href=\"https://collections.mfa.org/objects/151092\" target=\"_blank\">https://collections.mfa.org/objects/151092</a></p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 28.0761 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</a></li><li> Comstock and Vermeule 1976 57 no.89 ph <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002072</a></li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"><p>Elegant Hellenistic lettering, with serifs, small omicron above the line, sigma and mu with slightly diverging outer strokes, epsilon with shorter middle bar, kappa with short arms</p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  </div>",
